'''John McCarthy''' (born July 4, 1992) is an American [[association football|soccer]] player for the [[Tampa Bay Rowdies]] in the [[USL Championship]].

==Career==

===College and amateur===

McCarthy played four years of [[college soccer]] at [[La Salle University]] between 2010 and 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goexplorers.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=4994|title=Official Site of La Salle University Athletics|publisher=}}</ref>

While at college, McCarthy also appeared for [[Premier Development League|USL PDL]] clubs [[Ocean City Nor'easters]] in 2011 and 2012, and [[Reading United AC]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccerstats.us/bios/john-mccarthy/|title=John McCarthy – SoccerStats.us|publisher=}}</ref> He is La Salle's all-time leader among goalkeepers in saves (468), shutouts (28), and games played (75).

===Professional===
====Rochester Rhinos====
McCarthy signed his first professional deal with [[USL Pro]] club [[Rochester Rhinos]] on February 27, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goexplorers.com/news/2014/2/27/MSOC_0227145551.aspx|title=La Salle University Athletics – John McCarthy Inks Professional Contract With Rochester Rhinos Of USL|work=La Salle University}}</ref>
After the 2014 season, McCarthy was named the Rhinos' Rookie of the Year as he led the league with a 0.72 goals against average.

McCarthy was named [[2014 USL Pro season#League Awards|USL PRO Goalkeeper of the Year]] and [[2014 USL Pro season#League Awards|USL PRO Rookie of the Year]] for his notable 2014 season performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/direct-kicks/2014/09/26/rhinos-rookie-mccarthy-named-usls-goalkeeper-of-year/16279197/|title=Rhinos rookie McCarthy named USL PRO's Goalkeeper and Rookie of Year|publisher=The Tennessean|date=September 26, 2014|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>

====Philadelphia Union====
[[Image:John_McCarthy_kicks.jpg|thumb|200px|left]]
In 2015, McCarthy signed to his hometown club, [[Philadelphia Union]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/thegoalkeeper/Union-sign-Philly-native-John-McCarthy-as-3rd-GK-Andre-Blake-has-knee-surgery.html|title=Union sign Philly native John McCarthy as 3rd GK; Andre Blake has knee surgery|publisher=philly.com|date=February 23, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> Originally signed as a third goalkeeper behind first round draft pick, [[Andre Blake]], and designated player, [[Rais M'Bohli]], McCarthy was given a starting role as a result of injury and poor form, respectively. He made his [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] debut as the starter for the Union on April 11, 2015 versus [[New York City FC]]. McCarthy was heralded for his performance which resulted in his first win in the top flight as well as the Union's first win of [[2015 Philadelphia Union season|2015 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2015-04-11-philadelphia-union-vs-new-york-city-fc/recap|title=Philadelphia Union 2, New York City FC 1 &#124; MLS Match Recap|publisher=MLSSoccer.com|date=April 11, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref> McCarthy started 8 league matches during the 2015 season, posting one shutout. He was played mostly during the Union's [[2015 Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup|2015 U.S. Open Cup run]], earning wins in the first four rounds of competition (including two penalty shootouts) ultimately losing in the [[2015 Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup Final|final]]. On July 6, 2017, McCarthy started in an away game against Sporting Kansas City which resulted in a 1-1 draw. McCarthy made five noteworthy saves in the game, including an excellent foot save on Latif Blessing in the 70th minute.

McCarthy was released by Philadelphia at the conclusion of the 2018 season.

====Bethlehem Steel FC====
For the 2016 season, McCarthy played on loan to the Union's [[United Soccer League|USL]] club, [[Bethlehem Steel FC]]. He made 11 starts for the club and posted 5 shutouts for Steel FC's [[2016 Bethlehem Steel FC season|inaugural season]].

====Tampa Bay Rowdies====
John signed with the [[Tampa Bay Rowdies]] on January 31, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rowdies Sign Goalkeeper John McCarthy |url=https://www.rowdiessoccer.com/news_article/show/990548 |website=RowdiesSoccer.com |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref>

